Date: 2/3/1895
Source: Tuapeka Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: During the last month or two it had been reported that they were to pay the district a surprise visit, and the sly grog-sellers were in consequence more than usually careful. This accounts for the poor success that rewarded the efforts of the police. Neither at Kelso nor Tapanui were they successful in finding evidence of sly groggery in the houses visited by them.
Notes:

Date: 22/10/1910
Source: NZ Truth
Author:
Vol / Page: 8
Edition:
Quote:  It was shown that Orr was a prosperous, large-hearted resident who entertained his friends lavishly, notwithstainding the Prohibition blight on the township, and as there was no evidence of a sale, or storage for sale, or even a hint that Orr would blast his prosperous business by engaging in sneaking sly-groggery, Magistrate Day hurled the information out with so much force that it doubled up the local Prohibition League, which was removed to the nearest parsonage for repairs.
